Should have gotten an Italian beef,  because the hamburgers were awful. I mean,  terrible. Horrible,  bland,  over-cooked, flavorless pieces of meat in between 2 dried out buns; even the bacon was crunchy and lacked flavor. Wouldn't be surprised if it was pre-cooked. They obviously have no clue what medium rare is,  however, without even salt or pepper in the meat I doubt it would have made much difference. Fries also lacked any flavor. Virtually no salt. Granted these were ordered via the Eat247 app, so, it wasn't as fresh as it could have been,  but,  I'm taking that into account. It was still likely one of the worst burgers I've ever eaten. That includes fast food chains

I really think it's the best beef in the city. Ya know how you like one item and you decide to add another one just because. Well I did that, I ordered a cheeseburger and it came on what I would call an onion bun. Well the cheeseburger was good but the bun added a too much bread experience. That bun would be great for a double cheeseburger. Plus I think I was overcharged. The bill came to $15 and some tax, when I got home and did the numbers it the total should have been $13.4 and tax. Oh well with the taxes in Chicago sky high the number was probably right. I would still recommend this place to anyone who wants a good beef sandwich.
